            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Schedule III uses a vertical format with equity and liabilities first, then assets, each split into non-current and current. Equity share capital and other equity come first, then non-current liabilities, current liabilities, then property plant and equipment, other non-current assets and current assets. Items follow order of permanence rather than liquidity, with prior year figures alongside."
